🧭 nook — Agent Build Spec (Copy/Paste)
🎯 Mission Statement

nook addresses the loneliness epidemic by turning shared intent into shared physical presence, facilitating in-person spaces where people with similar goals can work, create, and grow together in low-pressure environments.

🧠 Product Summary

nook is an in-person coordination platform that matches people based on:

shared interests (writing, studying, coding, fitness, etc.)
location proximity
time availability

Users join or create Sessions, which represent scheduled real-world meetups at physical venues like cafés, libraries, or coworking spaces.

The system is designed for low-pressure co-presence, not social networking or messaging.

🧱 Core Concept

Session = the central unit of the system

A session is a scheduled event where users meet in person to work or create together.

Everything revolves around:

users joining sessions
showing up at physical venues
optional collaboration, no forced interaction
🔁 Core Data Flow
User opens React app
User selects interests (e.g., writing, coding)
System shows nearby sessions or allows session creation
User joins a session
Session is tied to:
venue (café/library/etc.)
time window
interest category
User physically travels to venue
User checks in using GPS validation
Other users also check in → shared co-presence begins
Users optionally work, collaborate, or simply co-exist
🧭 System Architecture
Frontend
React (web or mobile)
Responsibilities:
authentication UI
session discovery
session creation/joining
venue selection (map/list)
GPS check-in
Backend
Spring Boot monolith API

Modules:

User Module
auth, profile, interests
Session Module (core)
create session
join session
manage session lifecycle
Matching Module
match users by interest + location + time
Venue Module
cafés, libraries, coworking spaces
geo-coordinates
Check-in Module
GPS-based presence verification
Database (PostgreSQL)

Core entities:

Users
Interests
User_Interests
Sessions
Session_Participants
Venues
Checkins
External Integrations
Google Maps API (venue discovery + distance)
JWT Auth (authentication)
Push notifications (session reminders)
🧠 Design Constraints
No social feed
No messaging system (optional later, but NOT MVP)
No follower/friend graph
No content posting system

This is NOT a social media platform.

🎯 MVP Scope

Build only:

User authentication
Interest selection
Session creation
Session browsing (by interest + location)
Join session
Venue selection
GPS check-in
🔥 Key Product Principle

The product is not about communication—it is about coordinated physical presence.

🧪 Success Criteria

The MVP is successful if:

users can reliably find sessions
users actually meet in person
sessions lead to sustained co-working / co-creation behavior
